.TH "WINIX" "1" "2026\-04\-11" "Winix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
winix \- install, update, and uninstall Winix tools
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]winix\f[R] \f[I]command\f[R] [\f[I]tools\f[R]\&...]
[\f[I]options\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Cross\-platform installer for the Winix CLI tool suite.
Installs, updates, and uninstalls all Winix tools by delegating to your
platform\(cqs native package manager (Scoop or Winget on Windows;
Homebrew or direct download on macOS/Linux).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\f[B]install\f[R] [\f[I]tools\f[R]\&...]
Install all Winix tools, or a named subset.
.TP
\f[B]update\f[R]
Update all installed Winix tools.
.TP
\f[B]uninstall\f[R] [\f[I]tools\f[R]\&...]
Uninstall all Winix tools, or a named subset.
.TP
\f[B]list\f[R]
List all available Winix tools.
With \f[B]\(enjson\f[R], emits a JSON envelope on stdout instead of the
human\-readable table.
.TP
\f[B]status\f[R]
Show install status and version of each tool.
With \f[B]\(enjson\f[R], emits a JSON summary envelope on stdout instead
of the one\-line text summary.
.TP
\f[B]agents\f[R] \f[I]verb\f[R]
Manage the marker\-delimited Winix discoverability pointer in a
project\(cqs \f[B]AGENTS.md\f[R] (and \f[B]CLAUDE.md\f[R] when
applicable).
\f[I]verb\f[R] is one of \f[B]init\f[R], \f[B]status\f[R], or
\f[B]remove\f[R].
\f[B]init\f[R] \(em write or refresh the managed block.
\f[B]AGENTS.md\f[R] is always a target; \f[B]CLAUDE.md\f[R] is added
when it already exists or \f[B]\(enclaude\f[R] is given.
The block embeds a version\-pinned URL; re\-running at the same version
is byte\-stable.
Supports \f[B]\(enpath\f[R], \f[B]\(enclaude\f[R],
\f[B]\(endry\-run\f[R], \f[B]\(enjson\f[R].
\f[B]status\f[R] \(em report whether the block is present and current.
Exits 0 if current, 1 if absent or stale in any applicable file.
Supports \f[B]\(enpath\f[R], \f[B]\(enclaude\f[R], \f[B]\(enjson\f[R].
\f[B]remove\f[R] \(em strip the managed block from all applicable files.
Supports \f[B]\(enpath\f[R], \f[B]\(enclaude\f[R],
\f[B]\(endry\-run\f[R], \f[B]\(enjson\f[R].
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\(envia\f[R] \f[I]PM\f[R]
Force a specific package manager: \f[B]scoop\f[R], \f[B]winget\f[R],
\f[B]dotnet\f[R], \f[B]brew\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\(enpath\f[R] \f[I]DIR\f[R]
For \f[B]agents\f[R]: project directory to operate on (default: current
directory).
.TP
\f[B]\(enclaude\f[R]
For \f[B]agents\f[R]: include \f[B]CLAUDE.md\f[R] as a target even when
it does not already exist.
.TP
\f[B]\(endry\-run\f[R]
Print what would be done without executing any changes.
.TP
\f[B]\(enjson\f[R]
For \f[B]list\f[R] and \f[B]status\f[R], emit a JSON envelope on stdout
(suite convention) rather than the human\-readable table or summary.
The envelope includes the winix version, current platform, and per\-tool
install state; pipe through \f[B]jq\f[R] for scripted consumption.
Ignored on \f[B]install\f[R], \f[B]update\f[R], and \f[B]uninstall\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\(endescribe\f[R]
Print machine\-readable metadata and exit.
.TP
\f[B]\(encolor\f[R][=\f[I]WHEN\f[R]]
Coloured output: auto (default when omitted), always, or never.
.TP
\f[B]\(enno\-color\f[R]
Disable coloured output.
.TP
\f[B]\(enversion\f[R]
Show version.
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\(enhelp\f[R]
Show help.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Success \(em all requested operations completed.
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
One or more tools failed to install, update, or uninstall.
.TP
\f[B]125\f[R]
Usage error (bad arguments or unrecognised command).
.TP
\f[B]126\f[R]
Cannot execute \(em no supported package manager found.
.TP
\f[B]127\f[R]
Internal error (also: \f[B]agents\f[R] I/O failure).
.PP
For the \f[B]agents\f[R] subcommand, exit 1 means the discoverability
block is absent or stale (use \f[B]winix agents init\f[R] to fix); 125
means bad arguments or the path is not a directory.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\f[B]NO_COLOR\f[R]
If set, disables coloured output (no\-color.org).
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
winix install

winix install timeit peep

winix update

winix uninstall

winix list

winix status

winix install \-\-via scoop

winix install \-\-dry\-run

winix agents init

winix agents status

winix agents init \-\-path /path/to/project \-\-claude \-\-dry\-run
.EE
